The paper deals with the problem of computing accurate point-to-point correspondences among a set of human face scans with varying expressions. This problem is related to computer vision (cs.CV) as it involves processing and analyzing 3D face models. The approach used in the paper involves learning the locations of a set of landmarks present in a database, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The approach also uses a blendshape model to accurately fit the expression of the template to the expression of the scan, which is related to computer graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.LG, and cs.AI.
